---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="Glossary | Dear Bug Diary">
  <article>
    <p class="eyebrow">Glossary</p>
    <h1>Words Bugsy keeps underlined</h1>
    <p>Plain definitions for common QA terms used around the diary.</p>
  </article>

  <ul class="definition-list">
    <li>
      <strong>Regression Test:</strong>
      A test that checks whether previously working behavior still works after changes.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Regression Asset:</strong>
      A reusable test scenario, checklist, data set, or evidence pattern created from a past bug or risk.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Flaky Test:</strong>
      A test that sometimes passes and sometimes fails without a clear product change.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Test Evidence:</strong>
      Screenshots, logs, reports, outputs, or other proof that supports a test result.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Green Pipeline:</strong>
      A CI/CD or automation pipeline that passed its configured checks.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Human Review Checkpoint:</strong>
      A place where a person must review the result because automation alone is not enough.
    </li>
    <li>
      <strong>Suspiciously Green Pipeline:</strong>
      A pipeline that passes so cleanly that Bugsy starts wondering what it did not check.
    </li>
  </ul>
</BaseLayout>
